# 🧠 Team Responsibilities

This project is divided into **5 core modules**, each mapped to one team.

---

## 🟦 Team 1 – Data Uploading & Field Management

📌 Core Responsibility: **Data Foundation of the Platform**

### Features:
- Upload CSV, XLS, XLSX files
- Clean and validate headers
- Create custom fields (Text, Email, Phone, Date, etc.)
- Add records manually via UI
- Strong validation & error handling
- Accessibility-friendly forms

### Tech Focus:
- File parsing
- Data validation
- Database schema design (PostgreSQL)
- Multi-tenant data handling

---

## 🟩 Team 2 – Email Editor (Content Creation)

📌 Core Responsibility: **Email Design System**

### Features:
- Rich text editor (WYSIWYG)
- Font styling, colors, spacing
- Lists, links, images, attachments
- Section-based layouts
- Personalization tokens (e.g., {{name}})
- AI-assisted content (optional)
- Accessibility checks (alt text, contrast)

### Tech Focus:
- Editor frameworks (Tiptap / CKEditor / TinyMCE)
- Template engine (MJML / React Email)
- UI/UX design

---

## 🟨 Team 3 – Email Testing & Preview

📌 Core Responsibility: **Quality Assurance Before Sending**

### Features:
- Email preview (Desktop & Mobile)
- Simulate different email clients
- Send test emails
- Validate personalization rendering

### Tech Focus:
- Rendering engine
- Preview system
- Email testing logic

---

## 🟥 Team 4 – Email Sending & Scheduling

📌 Core Responsibility: **Campaign Execution Engine**

### Features:
- Sender name & email management
- Recipient selection (lists / individual)
- Subject & preview text with tokens
- Send now / schedule later
- Time-zone support
- Email queue system
- Integration with providers (SES, SendGrid)

### Tech Focus:
- Background jobs (RabbitMQ / SQS)
- Email APIs
- Scheduling systems
- Scalability

---

## 🟪 Team 5 – Analytics & Reporting

📌 Core Responsibility: **Performance Tracking & Insights**

### Features:
- Track: Sent, delivered, opened, clicked
- Bounce tracking (hard/soft)
- Open rate, click rate
- Time spent on email
- Click heatmaps
- Dashboard visualization

### Tech Focus:
- Event ingestion (webhooks)
- Data aggregation
- Charts (Recharts / Chart.js)
- Analytics queries

