# 🌿 Git Workflow Guide for All Teams

**CRITICAL:** Each team MUST work on its own dedicated branch. Never push directly to `main`.

---

## 📋 Team Branches

| Team | Branch Name |
|------|-------------|
| Team 1 | `feature/team1-data-upload` |
| Team 2 | `feature/team2-email-editor` |
| Team 3 | `feature/team3-testing-preview` |
| Team 4 | `feature/team4-sending-scheduling` |
| Team 5 | `feature/team5-analytics-reporting` |

---

## 🚀 Essential Git Commands

### 1️⃣ Initial Setup

```bash
# Clone repository
git clone https://github.com/Rahul-pamula/email_engine.git
cd email_engine

# List all branches
git branch -a

# Switch to your team's branch
git switch feature/team1-data-upload
```

### 2️⃣ Before Starting Work

```bash
# Verify you're on the right branch
git branch

# Pull latest changes from main
git pull origin main

# Continue on your team's branch
git switch feature/team1-data-upload
```

### 3️⃣ During Development

```bash
# Check modified files
git status

# Stage all changes
git add .

# Or stage specific files
git add src/components/FileUpload.tsx

# Commit with clear message
git commit -m "Add CSV file upload functionality"

# Push ONLY to your team's branch
git push origin feature/team1-data-upload
```

### 4️⃣ Sync Before Pushing

```bash
# Pull latest main to avoid conflicts
git pull origin main

# Push your updated branch
git push origin feature/team1-data-upload
```

### 5️⃣ Create Pull Request

```bash
# After pushing, go to GitHub
# https://github.com/Rahul-pamula/email_engine/pulls

# Click "New Pull Request"
# Base: main
# Compare: feature/team1-data-upload
# Add description and request reviewers
```

---

## ✅ Best Practices

✔️ **DO:**
- Work only on your team's branch
- Pull from `main` regularly
- Write clear commit messages
- Test before committing
- Create PRs for code review

❌ **DON'T:**
- Push to `main` directly
- Work on other team's branches
- Force push without approval
- Use vague commit messages

